						<summary>

						<p>Two sides (other) of a pillar built into the platform of the <hi rend="italic">Āshur-khāna.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1482, Raudri, Āshāḍha śu. 11, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to 1560 A.D. July 3.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. It seems to register some gift to god Nimirti Saṅgamēśvara by Chennama Kṛishṇama Nāyaniṁgā, son of Rānēḍu and grandson of Mudulagurti Likinēḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
